<body>
  <HeaderEn />
  <main class="page-main">
    <section class="page-hero page-hero--pricing">
      <div class="page-hero-bg" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="page-hero-overlay" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="page-hero-inner">
        <div class="page-label">Legal Fees · LEGAL FEES</div>
        <h1>Transparent Fees. No Hidden Costs.</h1>
        <p>Miao He offers transparent pricing with no hidden fees.</p>
        <p>Initial consultation $220 + HST; uncontested divorce from $2,000; separation agreements, prenuptial agreements, and other family law agreements from $2,500; contested family law matters billed hourly in 6-minute units.</p>
        <p>Before you sign a Retainer Agreement, Miao He will explain the applicable fee structure, likely costs, and estimated fee ranges based on your matter — so you can understand the costs and risks and decide whether to retain counsel on a fully informed basis.</p>
        <p class="page-last-updated page-last-updated--warm">Page last updated: June 19, 2026</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pricing-section">
      <div class="pricing-inner fade-in-section">
        <h2 class="section-subtitle section-subtitle--first">Common Services &amp; Fees</h2>
        <div class="pricing-table-wrap">
          <table class="pricing-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">Service</th>
                <th scope="col">Fee</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Initial consultation (30 minutes)</td>
                <td>$220 + HST</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Uncontested divorce</td>
                <td>$2,000 – $3,500 + HST + Disbursements</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Separation, prenuptial, cohabitation agreements, etc.</td>
                <td>$2,500 – $4,500 + HST + Disbursements</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Family law litigation</td>
                <td>Hourly billing</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Limited Retainer</td>
                <td>Billed based on actual work performed</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pricing-inner pricing-inner--consult">
        <div class="consult-intro-layout consult-intro-motion-root">
          <div class="consult-intro-content consult-intro-slide consult-intro-slide--left">
            <div class="pricing-card highlight">
              <h2>Initial Consultation</h2>
              <div class="pricing-amount">$220 <span>+ HST</span></div>
              <div class="pricing-detail">30 minutes · Mandarin &amp; English · In person or video</div>
              <p>Many clients' first questions when contacting a lawyer are:</p>
              <div class="pricing-includes pricing-includes--dark">
                <ul>
                  <li>Do I have a viable case?</li>
                  <li>Should I negotiate or litigate?</li>
                  <li>How much is this likely to cost?</li>
                  <li>What steps lie ahead?</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <p>The purpose of an initial consultation is not only to understand the facts, but to help you understand your legal position, potential risks, and available options.</p>
              <p>During the consultation, Miao He will:</p>
              <div class="pricing-includes pricing-includes--dark">
                <ul>
                  <li>Analyse the facts and legal issues</li>
                  <li>Explain court procedures and timelines</li>
                  <li>Discuss the pros and cons of litigation vs. settlement</li>
                  <li>Provide a preliminary fee estimate</li>
                  <li>Answer your most pressing legal questions</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <p>For many clients, the greatest value after a consultation is not a single answer — but finally seeing the overall direction of the matter and how to plan the next step.</p>
              <a href="tel:6479306688" class="btn-primary">📞 647-930-6688</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="consult-intro-visual consult-intro-slide consult-intro-slide--right">
            <div class="consult-intro-visual-frame">
              <img src="/images/office-meeting.png" alt="" width="1200" height="800" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pricing-inner fade-in-section">
        <h2 class="section-subtitle">Uncontested Divorce</h2>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-amount-sm">$2,000 – $3,500 <span>+ HST + Disbursements</span></div>
          <p>For matters where both parties have already agreed on divorce-related issues and only need the divorce process completed.</p>
          <p>Unlike some lawyers who only prepare documents, we follow the matter through until the divorce process is complete.</p>
          <div class="pricing-includes">
            <div class="includes-title">Services include:</div>
            <ul>
              <li>Review of the parties' agreement</li>
              <li>Preparation and filing of court documents</li>
              <li>Follow-up on court processing</li>
              <li>Obtaining the Divorce Order</li>
              <li>Assistance applying for the Divorce Certificate</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="pricing-includes" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
            <div class="includes-title">Fixed-fee conditions</div>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">Where both parties remain cooperative and the matter does not become contested, no additional legal fees are charged within the fixed fee.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0; margin-top: 0.5rem;">If the nature of the matter changes — for example, one party refuses to cooperate, new disputes arise, or additional steps are required — related costs will be discussed with you in advance.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pricing-inner fade-in-section">
        <h2 class="section-subtitle">Separation, Prenuptial &amp; Other Family Law Agreements</h2>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-amount-sm">$2,500 – $4,500 <span>+ HST + Disbursements</span></div>
          <p>This applies to:</p>
          <div class="pricing-includes">
            <ul>
              <li>Separation Agreement</li>
              <li>Prenuptial Agreement</li>
              <li>Marriage Contract</li>
              <li>Cohabitation Agreement</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>The value of an agreement is not measured on signing day, but whether it can withstand court scrutiny years — or even decades — later if a dispute arises.</p>
          <p>As a family litigation lawyer, Miao He reviews agreements from the perspective of potential future disputes, aiming to reduce the risk that an agreement is challenged or set aside.</p>
          <div class="pricing-includes">
            <div class="includes-title">Services include:</div>
            <ul>
              <li>Understanding both parties' financial circumstances and needs</li>
              <li>Legal advice</li>
              <li>Drafting the agreement</li>
              <li>Revising and negotiating terms</li>
              <li>Assisting with the signing process</li>
              <li>Coordinating Independent Legal Advice (ILA)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="pricing-note">✅ No additional legal fee if the agreement is signed within 3 months of drafting.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pricing-inner fade-in-section">
        <h2 class="section-subtitle">Family Law Litigation</h2>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-amount-sm">Hourly billing</div>
          <p>This applies to:</p>
          <div class="pricing-includes">
            <ul>
              <li>Contested divorce</li>
              <li>Property division</li>
              <li>Child custody and decision-making responsibility</li>
              <li>Parenting time</li>
              <li>Child support</li>
              <li>Spousal support</li>
              <li>Domestic violence-related proceedings</li>
              <li>Cross-border family law disputes</li>
              <li>Recovery of overseas assets</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>Family law litigation cannot be offered on a single fixed-fee basis for all cases.</p>
          <p>Total fees depend on:</p>
          <div class="pricing-includes">
            <ul>
              <li>Complexity of the dispute</li>
              <li>Cooperation from the other party</li>
              <li>Number of court steps</li>
              <li>Volume of document preparation</li>
              <li>Whether a trial is required</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="pricing-includes" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
            <div class="includes-title">How billing works</div>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Legal fees are billed by time. Each 6 minutes is one billing unit.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Billable work includes:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Legal research</li>
              <li>Document drafting</li>
              <li>Court appearances</li>
              <li>Pre-hearing preparation</li>
              <li>Communications with opposing counsel</li>
              <li>Mediation and settlement negotiations</li>
              <li>Client meetings</li>
              <li>Phone and email communications</li>
              <li>Document review</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>All time spent on your file is recorded and reflected on your invoice — no hidden charges.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pricing-inner fade-in-section">
        <h2 class="section-subtitle">Limited Retainer</h2>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-amount-sm">Billed based on actual work performed</div>
          <p>A Limited Retainer means the lawyer handles specific tasks in your matter — not the entire case.</p>
          <p>This may suit:</p>
          <div class="pricing-includes">
            <ul>
              <li>Self-represented litigants</li>
              <li>Document review only</li>
              <li>Legal advice only</li>
              <li>Drafting of specific court documents</li>
              <li>Appearance at a single hearing</li>
              <li>Matters near conclusion that need a specific final step</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>A limited retainer can help you control legal costs while obtaining professional support at critical stages.</p>
          <p>If you are considering self-representation but are unsure how to proceed, feel free to ask whether a limited retainer is appropriate for your situation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pricing-inner fade-in-section">
        <h2 class="section-subtitle">About Disbursements</h2>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <p>Disbursements are third-party costs paid on your behalf. They are separate from legal fees and itemized clearly on your invoice.</p>
          <div class="pricing-includes">
            <div class="includes-title">Ontario court fees</div>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Common court fees currently include:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Divorce Application Filing Fee: <strong>$224</strong></li>
              <li>Divorce Order Fee: <strong>$445</strong></li>
              <li>Divorce Certificate: <strong>$25</strong></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>These amounts are paid to the court, not to your lawyer. Court fee schedules may change; please refer to the court's latest published rates.</p>
          <div class="pricing-includes" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
            <div class="includes-title">Other common disbursements</div>
            <ul>
              <li>Process server fees</li>
              <li>Notarization and certification</li>
              <li>Translation and interpretation</li>
              <li>Business valuation reports</li>
              <li>Financial expert reports</li>
              <li>Government search fees</li>
              <li>Courier and mailing costs</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>All disbursements are itemized separately on your invoice — no hidden charges.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pricing-inner fade-in-section">
        <h2 class="section-subtitle">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="pricing-faq">
          <div class="pricing-faq-item">
            <h3 class="pricing-faq-q">How much does a divorce lawyer typically charge?</h3>
            <p class="pricing-faq-a">Generally, an uncontested divorce is typically $2,000 to $3,500 plus HST, court fees, and disbursements. Contested matters are usually billed hourly, and total fees vary depending on complexity and how the case progresses.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pricing-faq-item">
            <h3 class="pricing-faq-q">Is the initial consultation fee charged?</h3>
            <p class="pricing-faq-a">Generally, yes. The 30-minute initial consultation is $220 + HST. There is no obligation to retain counsel afterward.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pricing-faq-item">
            <h3 class="pricing-faq-q">Can I consult first before deciding whether to hire a lawyer?</h3>
            <p class="pricing-faq-a">Typically, yes. Many clients use an initial consultation to understand their situation, likely fee ranges, and legal risks before deciding whether to formally retain a lawyer.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pricing-faq-item">
            <h3 class="pricing-faq-q">If the matter ends early, will unused legal fees be refunded?</h3>
            <p class="pricing-faq-a">Under Law Society of Ontario rules, generally any unused portion of a prepaid retainer deposit — after deducting fees for work already completed — is typically returned to the client. The exact process depends on your retainer agreement and LSO requirements.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pricing-faq-item">
            <h3 class="pricing-faq-q">Can I retain a lawyer for only part of the work?</h3>
            <p class="pricing-faq-a">Generally, yes. A Limited Retainer typically allows you to retain counsel for specific tasks only, without full-case representation. The scope is set out in the Retainer Agreement.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="pricing-disclaimer">*Legal fees vary depending on the complexity and circumstances of each matter. The fee ranges above are for general reference only and do not constitute a quote for any specific case.*</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="page-cta fade-in-section">
      <h2>Our Commitment to Transparent Fees</h2>
      <p>Miao He believes clients have the right to understand likely costs and risks before retaining a lawyer.</p>
      <p>Before you sign a Retainer Agreement, Miao He will:</p>
      <ul class="page-cta-list">
        <li>Understand your matter</li>
        <li>Explain how fees are charged</li>
        <li>Outline likely costs</li>
        <li>Provide a reasonable fee estimate</li>
        <li>Discuss how different approaches may affect total cost</li>
      </ul>
      <p>A lawyer's role is not only to provide legal services, but to help clients make informed decisions based on cost, risk, and benefit.</p>
      <p><strong>Transparent fees. Clear communication. No hidden charges.</strong></p>
      <div class="cta-actions">
        <a href="tel:6479306688" class="btn-primary">📞 647-930-6688</a>
        <a href="mailto:miao@miaohelaw.ca" class="btn-secondary">miao@miaohelaw.ca</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer lang="en" />
  <script is:inline>
    (function () {
      var els = document.querySelectorAll('.fade-in-section');
      if (els.length) {
        if (!('IntersectionObserver' in window)) {
          els.forEach(function (el) {
            el.classList.add('is-visible');
          });
        } else {
          var io = new IntersectionObserver(
            function (entries) {
              entries.forEach(function (entry) {
                if (entry.isIntersecting) {
                  entry.target.classList.add('is-visible');
                  io.unobserve(entry.target);
                }
              });
            },
            { threshold: 0.15 }
          );
          els.forEach(function (el) {
            io.observe(el);
          });
        }
      }

      var consultRoot = document.querySelector('.consult-intro-motion-root');
      if (consultRoot) {
        if (!('IntersectionObserver' in window)) {
          consultRoot.classList.add('consult-intro-visible');
        } else {
          var consultIo = new IntersectionObserver(
            function (entries) {
              entries.forEach(function (entry) {
                if (entry.isIntersecting) {
                  entry.target.classList.add('consult-intro-visible');
                  consultIo.unobserve(entry.target);
                }
              });
            },
            { threshold: 0.2 }
          );
          consultIo.observe(consultRoot);
        }
      }
    })();
  </script>
</body>
</html>

<style>
  .page-main { max-width: 100%; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
